<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-28T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-28T03:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2–2849: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-28T16:00:00+08:00">February
                                    28, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 28—8:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>486. Reliably informed Sun Fo arriving here this afternoon following
                            receipt of message from Generalissimo “ordering” him Nanking. Sent
                            Department 486, repeated Canton 113, Shanghai 226.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>